To make your gummy ball
you will need some water, gelatin, jelly flavors,spherical mold and some fishing lines
Add roughly three tablespoons of gelatin to a hundred miles of water for one bowl
And boil until it's all dissolved
Then add a jelly flavoring until the color looks just right
Tie some knobs in the fishing line
and then pop into the mold leaving a loop coming around the top so you can hang it for your tree
Then pour your gummy mixture into the mold and leave it in the fridge to set
When it's set take it out of the mold and third a bubble top of the fishing line
And stick it into the gummy to make it looks super really sick

To make an eatable Christmas cone tree you will need a Waffle cone
some pliable icing and a decorative star
First step is to flatten the base of the cone so it will stand up right
You can break it off with your fingers or use a bread knife to gently sore it off
Then pipe your icing sugar all over the cone in a spiral shape until you reach the button
Then put a little bit in a top to hold your star and you are done
You might fool anyone with this by itself but in a group they probably will even notice that one of them looks lightly delicious

In order to make eatable Christmas foliage
You need some cherries sugar glue and eatable gold glitter
Just paint the surface of the cherry with glue and then dust it with the glitter and you are done!
And a great way to cut the cherry is to roll it around gently in the glitter
And also if you combine sugar glue another method is actually to cut the surface with some egg white
When the glue dries your cherry will look identical to your decorations
And you will be ready to give someone a tasty surprise
